You have following proposal:
Introduction. [BIP-120]([link]) intended to remove a number of pools from the Gauge system. In the specification section, the list of gauges to kill was taken from data that did not include changes introduced by caps set in place in [BIP-66]([link]) and [BIP-57]([link]) As a result some of the pools intended to be killed still have active gauges. This BIP seeks to reconcile the current state with the desired state, and requests permission to execute on-chain commands to kill remaining gauges that were missed in BIP-120. A total of 9 gauges were found to still be active from the list originally intended by BIP-120. For a detailed view of the reconciliation check the table here on [Notion]([link]) Specification: If approved, the DAO Multisig '[hexadecimals]' will interact with the 'AuthorizerAdaptor' at '[hexadecimals]' and call 'performAction' using kill_gauge '[hexadecimals]' for the 'data(bytes)' argument and the above list of contracts for the 'target(address)' argument. This call will be run 9 times, with each of the following target addresses: 'json. { "POLY: Balancer 20USDC-40TEL-40DFX RewardGauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "Balancer NWWP Gauge Deposit (NOTE/WETH 50/50)": "[hexadecimals]", "Balancer 50N/A-50N/A Gauge Deposit (D2D/BAL 50/50)": "[hexadecimals]", "Balancer 20DAI-80TCR Gauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "Balancer 20WETH-80HAUS Gauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "ARBI: Balancer B-80PICKLE-20WETH RewardGauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "ARBI: Balancer 20WETH-80CRE8R RewardGauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "POLY: Balancer TELX-60TEL-20BAL-20USDC RewardGauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", "POLY: Balancer TELX-50TEL-50BAL RewardGauge Deposit": "[hexadecimals]", }
